006package gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.model;
007
008import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.util.ObjectUtils;
009
010import java.util.Collection;
011
012import javax.xml.namespace.QName;
013
014import edu.umd.cs.findbugs.annotations.NonNull;
015import edu.umd.cs.findbugs.annotations.Nullable;
016
017/**
018 * Represents a definition that may contain flags.
019 *
020 * @param <FI>
021 *          the flag instance Java type
022 */
023public interface IFeatureContainerFlag<FI extends IFlagInstance> extends IModelDefinition {
024  /**
025   * Lazy initialize the flag instances associated with this definition.
026   *
027   * @return the flag container
028   */
029  @NonNull
030  IContainerFlagSupport<FI> getFlagContainer();
031
032  @Override
033  @Nullable
034  default FI getFlagInstanceByName(QName name) {
035    return getFlagContainer().getFlagInstanceMap().get(name);
036  }
037
038  @Override
039  @NonNull
040  default Collection<? extends FI> getFlagInstances() {
041    return ObjectUtils.notNull(getFlagContainer().getFlagInstanceMap().values());
042  }
043
044  @Override
045  default FI getJsonKey() {
046    return getFlagContainer().getJsonKeyFlagInstance();
047  }
048}
